quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  40,67,"He it is Who created you from dust, then from a drop, then from a blood clot. Then He brings you forth as infants, that you may then reach maturity, then that you may grow old—though some of you are taken earlier—that you may reach a term appointed, and that haply you may understand"
  40,68,"He it is Who gives life and causes death. So when He decrees a thing, He only says to it, “Be!” and it is"
  40,69,"Hast thou not considered those who dispute concerning the signs of God, how they are turned away"
  40,70,"those who deny the Book, and that wherewith We have sent Our messengers? But soon they will know"
  40,71,"since they will be dragged, with shackles and chains around their necks"
  40,72,into boiling liquid; then they will be set aflame in the Fire
  40,73,"Then it will be said unto them, “Where are those whom you used to ascribe as partners"
  40,74,"apart from God?” They will reply, “They have forsaken us. Nay, but we were not calling upon aught before.” Thus does God lead astray the disbelievers"
  40,75,“That is because you used to exult upon the earth without right and because you were insolent
  40,76,"Enter the gates of Hell, therein to abide.” How evil is the abode of the arrogant"
  40,77,"So be patient. Surely God’s Promise is true. And whether We show thee a part of that which We promise them, or We take thee, unto Us will they be returned"